The intern will assist the team in:

Gatekeeper and point person for the deal flow process;
Screening and reviewing investment opportunities;
Supporting the Partner in charge in the due diligence process, engaging with founders along with the fund Partners; collecting, organizing and analysing reported information;
Preparing Investment Memos to present to the Investment Committee;
Managing fund communication, including working on presentations and supporting its online presence and reach;
Undertaking ad hoc market research;
Attending and facilitating local events and liaising with other Seedstars teams.

The candidate should have:

A strong interest in the VC and investment space, in startups, as well as in emerging markets, and particularly Africa;
A prior internship experience in an investment fund, an investment bank, a management consultancy, or an audit firm. Experiences with leading scale-ups will also be considered;
Strong analytical and writing skills, with capacity to multi-task and meet deadlines;
A strong command of French (if based in Dakar or Abidjan) and English (both written and verbal);
Experience in using Office, including Excel.
